sentences: Matthew James Redman (born 14 February 1974) is an English Christian worship leader, singer-songwriter and author.
Co-written with Jonas Myrin, the single reached No. 1 on the US Billboard Christian Songs chart in 2012.
In 1993, Redman helped found Soul Survivor, a global Christian movement and yearly music festival aimed at youth alongside his pastor Mike Pilavachi.

In 2002, after a sabbatical in America to record Where Angels Fear to Tread, Redman moved to Brighton.

In August 2010, they returned to the UK with their children.
Matt recorded his first album, Wake Up My Soul, at ICC studios in January and February 1994.

On 28 July 2012, "10,000 Reasons (Bless the Lord)", the title track of Redman's new album, topped the Billboard Christian Songs chart, where it stayed for 13 weeks.

The single went on to win two Grammy Awards, for Best Contemporary Christian Music Song and Best Gospel/Contemporary Christian Music Performance and was certified Gold by RIAA in 2018.

The album's success came immediately after Matt Redman and LZ7, a Manchester-based Christian rap and urban music group, released the song "Twenty Seven Million" on 27 February 2012, to raise awareness for the anti-human trafficking movement.
In 2019, Redman announced he had signed with Integrity Music, with new music coming in late 2019, and a new album in 2020.
